                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;@supercat My &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/questions/3730019/why-not-use-double-or-float-to-represent-currency/25251702?noredirect=1#comment53587892_25251702&quot;&gt;comment&lt;/a&gt; emphasizes using a binary FP of the smallest monetary unit or a decimal FP both incur similar rounding issues - like in your comment with &quot;and divide, rounding to the nearest penny&quot;.  Using a base 2 or base 10 FP does not provide an advantage either way in your scenario.&lt;/span&gt;

